# No layout changes without explicit approval

Sam's hero nav and case-study layouts are fragile (flex sizing, gaps, vector rows, squiggles, reveal timing).

## Rule

**Do not change layout, spacing, sizing, flex, gaps, margins, or HTML structure** in `web-main/` (or `app/`) **unless Sam explicitly asks** for that change.

## What counts as a layout change

- Restructuring links (e.g. merging 8 word-links into 3 grouped links)
- CSS changes to `width`, `flex`, `column-gap`, `margin`, `top`, positioning
- JS that alters flex shares or row fitting (`fitHeroRows`, `hydrateSvgUnit` flex logic)
- Swapping row patterns (e.g. `hero-link-vector-words` vs one-link-per-word)

## Allowed without asking

- **Interaction-only** changes that preserve the exact DOM and computed layout (e.g. grouped hover via JS `mouseenter` on a wrapper, without moving or resizing elements)
- Bug fixes Sam reported, scoped to the broken behaviour only
- Changes Sam explicitly requested (e.g. "half the gap on contact row")

## When adding grouped hover

Keep the **working 8-link (one SVG per link) markup**. Add hover grouping in JS/CSS only — e.g. `data-hover-group` + sibling highlight — never merge links into `hero-link-vector-words` on the contact row unless Sam approves a layout change first.
